#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:19
msgid ""
"## Improve security If your YunoHost server is used in a critical production "
"environment, or if you want to improve its safety, you may want to follow "
"those good practices."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Attention:** *Following those instructions requires advanced knowledges in "
"system administration.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:24
msgid ""
"### SSH authentication via key By default, the SSH authentication uses the "
"administration password. Deactivation this kind of authentication and "
"replacing it by a key mechanism is advised."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "**On your client**:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:31
msgid ""
"```bash ssh-keygen ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub <your_yunohost_server> "
"```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:33
msgid "Type your admnistration password and your key will be copied on your server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**On your server**, edit the SSH configuration file, in order to deactivate "
"the password authentication.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:38 /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:55
msgid "```bash nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:42
msgid "# Modify or add the following line PasswordAuthentication no ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:44 /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:61 /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:109
msgid "Save and restart SSH daemon."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:48
msgid "### Modify SSH port"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:50
msgid ""
"To prevent SSH connection attempts by robots that scan the Internet for any "
"attempt SSH connections with any server accessible, you can change the SSH "
"port."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**On your server**, edit the ssh configuration file, in order to modify SSH "
"port.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:59
msgid ""
"# Search line \"Port\" and remplace port number (by default 22) by another "
"not used number Port 22 # to replace by 9777 for example ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:63
msgid "Then restart the iptables firewall and close the old port in iptables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:69
msgid ""
"```bash yunohost firewall reload yunohost firewall disallow "
"<your_old_ssh_port_number> # port by default 22 yunohost firewall disallow "
"--ipv6 TCP <your_new_ssh_port_number> # for ipv6 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:71
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**For the next SSH connections ** you need to add the `-p` option followed "
"by the SSH port number.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Sample**:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:77
msgid "```bash ssh -p <new_ssh_port_number> admin@<your_yunohost_server> ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:81
msgid "### Change the user authorized to connect via SSH"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:83
msgid ""
"To avoid multiple forcing the admin login attempts by robots, it can "
"possibly change the authorized user to connect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:87
msgid ""
"<div class=\"alert alert-info\" markdown=\"1\"> In the case of a key "
"authentication, brute force has no chance of succeeding. This step is not "
"really useful in this case </div>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:97
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**On your server**, add a user\n"
"```bash\n"
"sudo adduser user_name\n"
"```\n"
"Choose a strong password, since it is the user who will be responsible to "
"obtain root privileges.\n"
"Add the user to sudo group so just to allow him to perform maintenance tasks "
"that require root privileges.\n"
"```bash\n"
"sudo adduser user_namesudo\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:102
msgid ""
"Now, change the SSH configuration to allow the new user to connect.  **On "
"your server**, edit the SSH configuration file ```bash sudo nano "
"/etc/ssh/sshd_config"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:107
msgid ""
"# Look for the section \"Authentication\" and add at the end of it: "
"AllowUsers user_name ``` Only users listed in the AllowUsers directive will "
"then be allowed to connect via SSH, which excludes the admin user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:114
msgid ""
"### Disable YunoHost API YunoHost administration is accessible through an "
"**HTTP API**, served on the 6787 port by default. It can be used to "
"administrate a lot of things on your server, thus to break many things "
"between malicious hands. The best thing to do, if you know how to use the "
"[command-line interface](/moulinette), is to deactivate the `yunohost-api` "
"service."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/security.md:118
msgid "```bash sudo service yunohost-api stop ```"
msgstr ""

